<h2 class="heading-large">2. What is the deputy service?</h2>
<div class="text">
  <p>In order to use this service, you will need to enter information including names, addresses, other contact details, dates of birth and the relationship of involved parties to the client. We use this information to populate a report and for no other purpose. OPG doesn't see what you’ve entered into the service until you have submitted the report.</p>
  <p>Separately from the information entered by those using this service, OPG also collects site-usage information from this service This allows us to see how the service is being used so we can improve it. This information does not contain any personal data.</p>
  <p>We’ll only ever collect information that will help us make the site work better for you: information that will let us contact you if you’ve asked us to, let us give you accurate information if you need it, and give us a sense of how people are using the service, so we can keep improving it.</p>
  <p>You have the right as the owner of the account to delete it, or any and all information in it, at any point.</p>
</div>


<h2 class="heading-large text">3. What happens when I submit my report?</h2>
<div class="text">
  <p>When you click submit within the service a version of the annual report is sent to a mail box which is accessed by OPG and kept in accordance with the privacy policy.</p>
  <p>Within the application itself, any reports that have been submitted to the OPG can no longer be changed. But prior to the submission of the report, there is a ‘save and return’ functionality that gives the deputy the opportunity to change any information they have entered in the system. The save and return function will be explained at the beginning of the form.</p>
  <p>However, deputies are still able to request for their data to be corrected and the service’s terms and conditions will include information on how to correct data that has already been submitted through their deputy report.</p>
</div>


