<h3 class="heading-medium">How does the service keep your information safe?</h3>
<div class="text">
  <p>The OPG takes data security very seriously. We take every step to make sure that your data remains private and secure.</p>
  <p>The postcode lookup functionality within this service only returns information about the address in question. No other information is either sent to the service or returned from the service.</p>
  <p>We make every effort to check and test this service whenever we amend or update it. However, you must take your own precautions to ensure that the way you access this service does not expose you to the risk of viruses, malicious computer code or other forms of interference which may damage your own computer system.</p>
  <p>You stay signed in until you sign out, or until 20 minutes elapse from the time you close or navigate away from the service. This is in order to keep the service secure.</p>
</div>

<h3 class="heading-medium text">All data collected by this service is stored in our secure database and is kept within the European Economic Area (EEA).</h3>
<p class="text">However, due to the global nature of the internet, the data sent to and from the database may transit through countries outside of the EEA. Data isn’t stored in a non-EEA country.</p>

<h3 class="heading-medium">Will the service share my information?</h3>
<div class="text">
  <p>We never share your information with other organisations for marketing, market research or commercial purposes and won’t pass on your personal information to any other websites.</p>
  <p>However, we may share your contact details with GOV.UK Notify. Notify is a secure government service that allows us to message you about your deputyship via text, email or post, quickly and cost effectively. </p>
  <p>Neither Notify nor its SMS, email and post providers will use your personal information for direct marketing. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/govuk-notify/govuk-notify" target="_blank">Find out more about Notify</a>.</p>
</div>

<h3 class="heading-medium">Who has access to the service?</h3>
<p class="text">Our hosting provider (Amazon Web Services) and Ministry of Justice (MoJ) staff are responsible for supporting the service and have access to the secure database in which all information entered into this service will be stored. All staff who have access to the secure data have MoJ security clearance.</p>


